'''Youri Marion A. Tielemans''' (born 7 May 1997) is a Belgian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for {{English football updater|AstonVil}} club [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]] and [[Captain (association football)|captains]] the [[Belgium national football team|Belgium national team]].

Tielemans began his career at [[R.S.C. Anderlecht|Anderlecht]], where he made 185 official appearances and scored 35 goals across four seasons. He won the [[Belgian Pro League|league title]] twice and in 2017 was chosen as the [[Belgian professional football awards|Belgian Professional Footballer of the Year]]. He is the youngest Belgian to play in the [[UEFA Champions League]], making his debut in the competition at the age of 16 years and 148 days. After two years at [[AS Monaco|Monaco]] in [[Ligue 1]], he joined [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]] in 2019, initially on loan and then for an estimated fee of £33&nbsp;million. He played 195 total games and scored 28 goals, including the only goal of the [[2021 FA Cup final]]. In 2023, when his contract expired, he joined Aston Villa.

Tielemans represented Belgium at several youth levels and before gaining his first [[Cap (sport)|cap]] for [[Belgium national football team|the national team]] in November 2016, aged 19. He was part of the squad that came third at the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]], also featuring at [[UEFA Euro 2020]], the [[2022 FIFA World Cup|2022 World Cup]] and [[UEFA Euro 2024|Euro 2024]].

==Club career==
===Anderlecht===
[[File:Youri Tielemans 2016.jpg|thumb|upright|Tielemans playing for [[R.S.C. Anderlecht|Anderlecht]] in 2016]]

Tielemans is a youth product of [[R.S.C. Anderlecht|Anderlecht]]<ref>{{Cite web |last=Hall |first=Pete |date=13 April 2017 |title=Who is Youri Tielemans? We profile Anderlecht midfielder ahead of Man Utd clash |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11095/10832932/who-is-youri-tielemans-we-profile-anderlecht-midfielder-ahead-of-man-utd-clash |access-date=2025-04-12 |website=Sky Sports |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=UEFA.com's weekly wonderkid: Youri Tielemans |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/news/0253-0d042a008a7d-9b0c910cfefd-1000--uefa-com-s-weekly-wonderkid-youri-tielemans/ |access-date=2025-04-12 |publisher=UEFA |language=en}}</ref> and signed his first professional contract with the club at the age of 16.<ref>{{cite web|last1=De Cock|first1=Bjorn|title=In the footsteps of Vincent Kompany: Youri Tielemans|url=http://www.benefoot.net/in-the-footsteps-of-vincent-kompany-youri-tielemans/|website=Benefoot|access-date=13 April 2016|date=28 October 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150913041953/http://www.benefoot.net/in-the-footsteps-of-vincent-kompany-youri-tielemans/|archive-date=13 September 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref>

On 21 July 2013, he was included in the senior squad for the first time, remaining an unused substitute in the 1–0 win over [[KRC Genk|Genk]] in the [[2013 Belgian Super Cup]]. On 28 July 2013, he made his first-team debut in the opening round of the [[Belgian First Division A|Belgian Pro League]] season against [[K.S.C. Lokeren Oost-Vlaanderen|Lokeren]], replacing injured [[Sacha Kljestan]] after 25 minutes of a 2–3 home loss.<ref>{{cite news|title=Lokeren smeert jong Anderlecht al nederlaag aan|url=http://sporza.be/cm/sporza/matchcenter/mc_voetbal/2.28512/speeldag1/1.1685335|access-date=24 December 2016|publisher=Sporza|date=28 July 2013|language=nl|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161225080736/http://sporza.be/cm/sporza/matchcenter/mc_voetbal/2.28512/speeldag1/1.1685335|archive-date=25 December 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=28 July 2013 |title=AND 2–3 LOK {{!}} Anderlecht – Lokeren {{!}} Summary |url=https://www.flashscore.com/match/CIzXEDXn/#/match-summary/match-summary |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221125105306/https://www.flashscore.com/match/CIzXEDXn/#/match-summary/match-summary |archive-date=25 November 2022 |access-date=25 November 2022 |website=Flashscore}}</ref> This made him the fourth-youngest player in the league's history.<ref name=":1">{{Cite news |last=Morgan |first=Richard |date=2 November 2015 |title=Who is Youri Tielemans? We profile exciting Anderlecht midfielder |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11095/10052669/anderlecht-midfielder-youri-tielemans-profiled |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241214100915/https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11095/10052669/anderlecht-midfielder-youri-tielemans-profiled |archive-date=14 December 2024 |access-date=2025-04-12 |work=Sky Sports |language=en-GB |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 2 October 2013, he became the youngest Belgian player to play in the [[UEFA Champions League]], starting in a match against [[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiacos]] at the age of 16 years and 148 days.<ref>{{cite news |first=Berend |last=Scholten |title=UEFA.com's weekly wonderkid: Youri Tielemans |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/news/0253-0d042a008a7d-9b0c910cfefd-1000--uefa-com-s-weekly-wonderkid-youri-tielemans/ |publisher=[[UEFA]] |date=14 February 2015 |access-date=6 May 2015 }}</ref> He played 29 games – of which 21 starts – as Anderlecht won the [[2013–14 Belgian Pro League]], scoring to open a 3–0 win over [[Club Brugge KV|Club Brugge]] at the [[Constant Vanden Stock Stadium]] on 6 April 2014, a game in which he also assisted [[Cyriac]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Club go down 3–0 at Anderlecht|url=http://clubbrugge.be/en/news/game-reports/17958/club-gaat-met-3-0-onderuit-op-anderlecht?page=15|access-date=24 December 2016|publisher=Club Brugge|date=7 April 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161225000932/http://clubbrugge.be/en/news/game-reports/17958/club-gaat-met-3-0-onderuit-op-anderlecht?page=15|archive-date=25 December 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> Tielemans won the [[Belgian professional football awards#Young Professional Footballer of the Year|Belgian Young Player of the Year]] award in each of his first two seasons.<ref name=":1" />

Tielemans scored 13 times in 37 Belgian First Division A matches as Anderlecht won the [[2016–17 Belgian First Division A]]. He won the 2017 [[Ebony Shoe Award]] for best player of African origin,<ref name="ebony">{{cite web |date=8 May 2017 |title=Youri Tielemans verzilvert topstatus Ebbenhouten Schoen |url=http://www.hln.be/hln/nl/1284/Anderlecht/article/detail/3152483/2017/05/08/Youri-Tielemans-verzilvert-topstatus-Ebbenhouten-Schoen.dhtml |website=HLN}}</ref> and was named [[Belgian professional football awards|2016–17 Belgian Professional Footballer of the Year]].<ref name=gala>{{cite news|title=Gala du Footballeur Pro: Youri Tielemans élu joueur de l'année, René Weiler sacré entraîneur!|trans-title=Professional Footballer Awards: Youri Tielemans elected player of the year, René Weiler best manager!|url=http://www.dhnet.be/sports/football/division-1a/gala-du-footballeur-pro-youri-tielemans-elu-joueur-de-l-annee-rene-weiler-sacre-entraineur-photos-videos-59233294cd70022542fa3c48|access-date=5 September 2017|publisher=DH|date=22 May 2017|language=fr}}</ref> He scored 5 goals in 15 [[2016–17 UEFA Europa League]] matches, with his club reaching the quarter-finals, and was selected in its Squad of the Season.<ref>{{Cite web |title=UEFA Europa League Squad of the 2016/17 Season |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/news/0253-0d8227a747d5-c25ebf5c91c9-1000--uefa-europa-league-squad-of-the-2016-17-season/ |access-date=2025-04-12 |publisher=UEFA |language=en}}</ref>

===Monaco===
On 24 May 2017, Tielemans joined [[2016–17 Ligue 1]] champions [[AS Monaco FC|Monaco]] on a five-year deal for a fee of around €25&nbsp;million.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Officieel: Youri Tielemans tekent contract tot 2022 bij Franse kampioen Monaco |trans-title=Official: Youri Tielemans signs contract until 2022 with French champion Monaco |url=http://www.hln.be/hln/nl/1284/Voetbal/article/detail/3166600/2017/05/24/Officieel-Youri-Tielemans-tekent-contract-tot-2022-bij-Franse-kampioen-Monaco.dhtml |publisher=HLN |date=24 May 2017 |access-date=24 May 2017|language=nl}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |date=25 May 2017 |title=Youri Tielemans: Monaco sign highly-rated Belgian midfielder from Anderlecht |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/40042751 |access-date=2025-04-12 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Valente |first=Allan |date=24 May 2017 |title=Monaco have confirmed the signing of Youri Tielemans on a five-year deal |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11816/10891820/monaco-have-confirmed-the-signing-of-youri-tielemans-on-a-five-year-deal |access-date=2025-04-12 |website=Sky Sports |language=en}}</ref> He made his competitive debut on 29 July in the [[2017 Trophée des Champions|Trophée des Champions]] at the [[Grand Stade de Tanger]], playing the full 90 minutes in the 2–1 loss to [[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|Paris Saint-Germain]] and assisting [[Djibril Sidibé (footballer, born 1992)|Djibril Sidibé]]'s opening goal.<ref>{{cite news|last1=De Beck|first1=Mike|title=Tielemans meteen goed voor splijtende assist in eerste officiële wedstrijd|trans-title=Tielemans shows his worth with a clever assist in first official appearance|url=http://www.hln.be/hln/nl/1299/Ligue-1/article/detail/3220138/2017/07/29/Tielemans-meteen-goed-voor-splijtende-assist-in-eerste-officiele-wedstrijd.dhtml|access-date=5 September 2017|publisher=HLN|date=30 July 2017|language=nl}}</ref>

On 4 August 2017, Tielemans made his [[Ligue 1]] debut in the 3–2 home win over [[Toulouse FC|Toulouse]],<ref>{{Cite web |title=Monaco 3–2 Toulouse (4 Aug, 2017) Final Score – ESPN (UK) |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/match/_/gameId/482413/toulouse-as-monaco |access-date=2025-04-12 |publisher=ESPN |language=en}}</ref> coming on as a substitute for [[Radamel Falcao]] in the 87th minute. He made his [[UEFA competitions|UEFA club competition]] debut for Monaco on 13 September in the [[2017–18 UEFA Champions League group stage|UEFA Champions League group]] match away to [[RB Leipzig]], playing the full 90 minutes and registering his first competitive goal for Monaco by equalising in a 1–1 draw. On 16 September, Tielemans made his first Ligue 1 start and played the entire match in the 3–0 home win over [[RC Strasbourg Alsace|Strasbourg]], after having played a total of 56 minutes as a substitute in his first four Ligue 1 matches.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Ligue1.com – Monaco and Leipzig share Champions League spoils |url=http://www.ligue1.com/autresCompetitions/article/monaco-and-leipzig-share-champions-league-spoils.htm |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612135940/http://www.ligue1.com/autresCompetitions/article/monaco-and-leipzig-share-champions-league-spoils.htm |archive-date=12 June 2018 |access-date=2025-04-12 |website=ligue1.com |language=en |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=career data of Youri Tielemans|url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/yoeri-tielemans/297294/|publisher=Soccerway|date=16 September 2017}}</ref>

''[[France Football]]'' named Tielemans in their lists of the biggest flops of the first half of the season and the season overall.<ref>{{cite news |title=Youri Tielemans dans les flops de la première partie de saison en Ligue 1 |trans-title=Youri Tielemans among the flops of the first half of the Ligue 1 season|url=https://www.7sur7.be/7s7/fr/1760/Ligue-1/article/detail/3331832/2017/12/22/Youri-Tielemans-dans-les-flops-de-la-premiere-partie-de-saison-en-Ligue-1.dhtml |access-date=7 July 2018 |publisher=7sur7 |date=22 December 2017 |language=fr}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Vens |first1=Clint |title=Recordtransfer Anderlecht opgenomen in lijst grootste flops van de Ligue 1|trans-title=Anderlecht's record transfer included in list of Ligue 1's biggest flops |url=https://www.voetbalkrant.com/nl/nieuws/lees/2018-05-20/youri-tielemans-is-opgenomen-in-een-lijstje-met-grootste-flops-van-de-ligue-1 |access-date=7 July 2018 |publisher=Voetbalkrant |date=20 May 2018 |language=nl}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=19 March 2025 |title=10 years of NXGN: Youri Tielemans, Victor Osimhen & where 2016's best wonderkids are now {{!}} Goal.com |url=https://www.goal.com/en/lists/nxgn-2016-best-wonderkids/ugt5ciaielx911wusivtpvw6p |access-date=2025-04-12 |website=Goal (website) |language=en}}</ref> He scored his first Ligue 1 goal in his 31st game on 2 September 2018, in a 3–2 home loss to [[Olympique de Marseille|Marseille]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Buron |first1=Sébastien |title=Ligue 1 : Marseille arrache la victoire à Monaco|trans-title=Ligue 1: Marseille snatch victory from Monaco |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Ligue-1-marseille-arrache-la-victoire-a-monaco/936628 |access-date=19 May 2021 |newspaper=L'Équipe |date=2 September 2018 |language=fr}}</ref>

===Leicester City===
[[File:Youri Tielemans 2021.jpg|thumb|upright|Tielemans playing for [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]] in 2021]]

On 31 January 2019, Tielemans joined [[Premier League]] club [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]] on [[Loan (sports)|loan]] until the end of the season,<ref>{{Cite news |last=James |first=Stuart |date=31 January 2019 |title=Transfer deadline day roundup: Leicester sign Youri Tielemans on loan |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2019/jan/31/transfer-deadline-day-leicester-youri-tielemans |access-date=2025-04-12 |work=The Guardian |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |date=31 January 2019 |title=Youri Tielemans: Leicester confirm loan signing of Monaco midfielder |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/47068267 |access-date=2025-04-12 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> with [[Adrien Silva]] going the other way in a swap deal.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.90min.com/posts/6285456-leicester-complete-loan-signing-of-youri-tielemans-from-monaco-as-adrien-silva-departs|title=Leicester Complete Loan Signing of Youri Tielemans From Monaco as Adrien Silva Departs|date=31 January 2019|website=90min.com|language=en|access-date=31 January 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Youri Tielemans Joins On Loan As Adrien Silva Heads To Monaco |url=https://www.lcfc.com/news/999996/youri-tielemans-joins-on-loan-as-adrien-silva-heads-to-monaco/press-release |publisher=Leicester City F.C. |date=31 January 2019 |access-date=31 January 2019}}</ref> On 9 March, Tielemans scored his first goal for the club in a 3–1 win over [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]].<ref>{{Cite news |last=McNulty |first=Phil |date=8 March 2019 |title=Leicester 3–1 Fulham: Jamie Vardy double earns Brendan Rodgers first win |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/47424846 |access-date=2025-04-12 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> Tielemans completed a permanent move to Leicester City on 8 July 2019, on a four-year deal for an estimated fee of £32&nbsp;million.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Cooper |first1=Barry |last2=Davies |first2=Matt |last3=Kemble |first3=Jamie |title=City transfer news live – Youri Tielemans officially signs |url=https://www.leicestermercury.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/leicester-city-transfer-news-live-3065069 |newspaper=Leicester Mercury |access-date=8 July 2019 |date=8 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |date=8 July 2019 |title=Youri Tielemans: Leicester sign Monaco midfielder |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/48913144 |access-date=2025-04-12 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> He scored in a 3–1 home win over [[A.F.C. Bournemouth|Bournemouth]] on 31 August, but courted controversy with a high challenge on [[Callum Wilson (footballer, born 1992)|Callum Wilson]] that escaped punishment even after consultation with the [[video assistant referee]];<ref>{{cite news |title=Soccer-Bournemouth fume after Tielemans' rash tackle goes unpunished by VAR |url=https://uk.reuters.com/article/soccer-england-lei-bou/soccer-bournemouth-fume-after-tielemans-rash-tackle-goes-unpunished-by-var-idUKL3N25R07H |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190920132045/https://uk.reuters.com/article/soccer-england-lei-bou/soccer-bournemouth-fume-after-tielemans-rash-tackle-goes-unpunished-by-var-idUKL3N25R07H |url-status=dead |archive-date=20 September 2019 |access-date=20 September 2019 |publisher=Reuters |date=31 August 2019}}</ref> referees' chief [[Mike Riley (referee)|Mike Riley]] ruled that this was an incorrect decision and Tielemans should have been sent off.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Stone |first1=Simon |title=VAR: Four incorrect decisions fail to be overturned in Premier League |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/49683036 |access-date=20 September 2019 |work=BBC Sport |date=12 September 2019}}</ref>

On 15 May 2021, Tielemans scored the only goal of the [[2021 FA Cup Final]] with a long-range strike against [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] in the 63rd minute,<ref name=":2">{{Cite news |last=McNulty |first=Phil |date=14 May 2021 |title=Chelsea 0–1 Leicester: Foxes lift FA Cup for first time after Youri Tielemans stunner |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/57055571 |access-date=2025-04-12 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> sealing Leicester's first ever [[FA Cup]] title.<ref name=":2" /> He was named the [[man of the match]] and later won Leicester's Supporters’ Player of the Year and the Players’ Player of the Year awards.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Leicester City In 100 Players: Youri Tielemans |url=https://www.lcfc.com/pages/en/media-article/Leicester-City-In-100-Players:-Youri-Tielemans |access-date=2025-10-30 |website=www.lcfc.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|first=Phil|last=McNulty|title= Youri Tielemans produced one of the great FA Cup final goals to give Leicester City the trophy for the first time in their history with victory over Chelsea at Wembley|date=15 May 2021|publisher=BBC|url= https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/57055571|access-date=17 May 2021}}</ref>

In 2022, Tielemans was linked with a transfer to [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]], and there was speculation over whether he would sign a new contract.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Burlaga |first=Kate |date=2022-06-12 |title=Youri Tielemans admits Leicester exit 'not out of question' amid Arsenal interest |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/3490306/2022/06/07/youri-tielemans-admits-leicester-exit-not-out-of-question-amid-arsenal-interest/ |access-date=2025-10-30 |work=The New York Times |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last1=Tanner |first1=Rob |last2=Hay |first2=Anthony |date=2023-01-05 |title=Leicester should be brave enough to sell anyone who doesn't want to stay — Brendan Rodgers |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/4061909/2023/01/05/leicester-january-departures/ |access-date=2025-10-30 |work=The New York Times |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref> In June 2023, after Leicester's relegation from the Premier League, Tielemans announced he would be leaving the club.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-05-31 |title=Tielemans to leave Leicester following relegation |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/story/_/id/37769746/youri-tielemans-leave-leicester-premier-league-relegation |access-date=2025-10-30 |website=ESPN.com |language=en}}</ref>

=== Aston Villa ===
On 10 June 2023, Premier League club [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]] announced that they had reached an agreement to sign 26-year-old Tielemans on a free transfer, upon the expiry of his Leicester City contract on 1 July.<ref name=":0">{{cite news |date=10 June 2023 |title=Aston Villa announce Youri Tielemans agreement |url=https://www.avfc.co.uk/news/2023/june/10/villa-announce-tielemans-agreement/ |access-date=10 June 2023 |publisher=Aston Villa F.C.}}</ref> He made his debut on 12 August in the season opener, a 5–1 loss at [[Newcastle United]], in which he replaced the injured [[Leon Bailey]] at half time.<ref>{{cite news |title=Rampant Newcastle destroy Aston Villa as debutants make instant impact |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2023/08/12/newcastle-united-vs-aston-villa-premier-league-live-score/ |access-date=26 August 2023 |work=The Daily Telegraph |date=12 August 2023}}</ref>

On 26 October 2023, Tielemans scored his first goal for Aston Villa in a 4–1 away [[UEFA Europa Conference League]] victory over [[AZ Alkmaar]].<ref>{{cite web |date=26 October 2023 |title=AZ Alkmaar-Aston Villa {{!}} UEFA Europa Conference League 2023/24 |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaconferenceleague/match/2039328--az-alkmaar-vs-aston-villa/ |access-date=26 October 2023 |publisher=UEFA}}</ref>

At the end-of-season awards for the [[2024–25 Aston Villa F.C. season|2024–25 campaign]], Tielemans was voted both Supporters' and Players' Player of the Season for Aston Villa.<ref name=":5">{{cite news |date=21 May 2025 |title=Tielemans scoops End of Season Awards double |url=https://www.avfc.co.uk/news/2025/may/21/2025-player-awards-winners-men/ |access-date=22 May 2025 |publisher=Aston Villa F.C.}}</ref> On 20 May 2026, he opened the scoring in a 3–0 victory over [[SC Freiburg]] in the [[2026 UEFA Europa League final|Europa League final]], helping his club win their first title in the competition.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/news/02a5-20ac3759bba4-7f91e47690b9-1000--freiburg-0-3-aston-villa-rampant-villans-win-europa-leagu/ |title=Freiburg 0-3 Aston Villa: Brilliant Villans win Europa League for the first time |publisher=UEFA |date=20 May 2026}}</ref>

==International career==
[[File:Youri Tielemans 2018 (cropped 2).jpg|thumb|left|200px|Tielemans with [[Belgium national football team|Belgium]] during the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]].]]

In June 2015, Tielemans was called up to the senior [[Belgium national football team|Belgium]] squad for a [[UEFA Euro 2016 qualifying|UEFA Euro 2016 qualifier]] against [[Wales national football team|Wales]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Belgium's Marouane Fellaini out of Wales tie|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/32849871|access-date=13 November 2015|publisher=BBC|date=10 June 2015}}</ref> The 19-year-old finally made his senior international debut on 9 November 2016, in a 1–1 [[Exhibition game#Association football|friendly]] away draw to [[Low Countries derby|rival]] [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]], replacing [[Steven Defour]] in the 82nd minute.<ref>{{cite news|title=Netherlands 1–1 Belgium|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/37896400|access-date=23 December 2016|work=BBC Sport|date=10 November 2016}}</ref>

Tielemans was included in manager [[Roberto Martínez]]'s 23-man squad for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]] in Russia.<ref>{{cite news |title=World Cup 2018: Belgium include Vincent Kompany but Christian Benteke misses out |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/44353673 |access-date=7 July 2018 |work=BBC Sport |date=4 June 2018}}</ref> He played four matches in the tournament, including the 2–0 win over [[England national football team|England]] in the third-place match.<ref>{{cite news |last1=McNulty |first1=Phil |title=Belgium 2–0 England |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/44748604 |access-date=9 March 2019 |work=BBC Sport |date=14 July 2018}}</ref>

[[File:Youri Tielemans 2019.jpg|thumb|right|200px|Tielemans with [[Belgium national football team|Belgium]] in 2019.]]

Tielemans scored his first senior goal for Belgium on 21 March 2019, in a [[UEFA Euro 2020]] [[UEFA Euro 2020 qualifying|qualifying]] match against [[Russia national football team|Russia]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/47661854 |title=Belgium 3–1 Russia: Eden Hazard scores twice in Euro 2020 qualifier |date=21 March 2019 |website=[[BBC Sport]] |access-date=21 March 2019}}</ref> He was called up for the delayed final tournament in May 2021,<ref>{{Cite web |date=27 June 2021 |title=Belgium Euro 2020 squad: Full team profile |url=https://www.fourfourtwo.com/features/belgium-euro-2020-squad-the-complete-line-up-for-marchs-internationals |access-date=2025-04-12 |website=fourfourtwo.com |language=en}}</ref> and for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] in Qatar.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Lea |first1=Greg |title=Belgium World Cup 2022 squad and preview: Roberto Martinez announces final 26-man team |url=https://www.fourfourtwo.com/features/belgium-world-cup-2022-squad-players-line-up-qatar |access-date=30 July 2023 |work=FourFourTwo |date=1 December 2022}}</ref> At the latter tournament, he was substituted at half time for [[Amadou Onana]] as the team struggled to a 1–0 win over [[Canada men's national soccer team|Canada]] in their opening match.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Abbott |first1=Matt |title=Youri Tielemans moment goes viral as Alphonso Davies leaves Leicester City star on the floor |url=https://www.leicestermercury.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/youri-tielemans-moment-goes-viral-7856919 |access-date=30 July 2023 |work=Leicester Mercury |date=23 November 2022}}</ref> He was a substitute in the two other games of the group stage elimination, in which Onana and then [[Leander Dendoncker]] started alongside [[Axel Witsel]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Burton |first1=Chris |title=De Bruyne is right, the Golden Generation is over! Belgium winners, losers and ratings as Hazard struggles in shock Morocco loss |url=https://www.goal.com/en-gb/lists/de-bruyne-right-golden-generation-over-belgium-winners-losers-ratings-hazard-morocco/blt15d946c65d3ece0a |access-date=30 July 2023 |work=Goal (website) |date=27 November 2022}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Smith |first1=Peter |title=World Cup 2022 – Croatia 0–0 Belgium: Romelu Lukaku misses big chances as Roberto Martinez's 'golden generation' knocked out and Croatia reach last 16 |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11095/12757081/world-cup-2022-croatia-0-0-belgium-romelu-lukaku-misses-big-chances-as-roberto-martinezs-golden-generation-knocked-out-and-croatia-reach-last-16 |access-date=30 July 2023 |work=Sky Sports |date=2 December 2022}}</ref>

On 3 September 2025, Tielemans was appointed as the permanent captain of the Belgian national team by manager [[Rudi Garcia]].<ref>{{Cite news |date=2025-09-03 |title=Tielemans named as new Belgium captain |url=https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/tielemans-named-new-belgium-captain-2025-09-03/ |access-date=2025-09-03 |work=Reuters |language=en}}</ref>

==Style of play==
Tielemans began as a [[holding midfielder]], but was moved by Anderlecht manager [[Besnik Hasi]] to a more attacking role, where he scored long-range goals and was compared to [[Frank Lampard]] and [[Axel Witsel]].<ref name="sky">{{cite news |date=2 November 2015 |title=Who is Youri Tielemans? We profile exciting Anderlecht midfielder |url=http://www.skysports.com/football/news/11095/10052669/anderlecht-midfielder-youri-tielemans-profiled |access-date=24 December 2016 |publisher=Sky Sports}}</ref> A 2015 profile by [[Sky Sports]] noted his versatility as a [[Defensive midfielder|defensive]] or [[attacking midfielder]], concluding that his pace, passing and shot power suited the latter role better.<ref name=sky/> [[Paul Van Himst]], a former Anderlecht and Belgium player, noted at the same time that Tielemans had good skills with [[Long ball|long passes]].<ref name=sky/>

Primarily a box-to-box midfielder at Leicester,<ref>{{Cite web |last=Tudball |first=Rosie |date=23 April 2024 |title=Villa star has become 'indispensable' to Unai Emery, simply by adapting his game 🙌 |url=https://www.astonvilla.news/analysis/aston-villa-star-has-become-indispensable-to-unai-emery-simply-by-adapting-his-game/ |access-date=2025-04-12 |website=Aston Villa News |language=en-GB}}</ref> Tielemans has played frequently as a number 10 under Unai Emery at Aston Villa, frequently making progressive passes and recovering the ball for his team.<ref>{{Cite news |last1=Tanswell |first1=Jacob |last2=Harris |first2=Thom |date=12 September 2024 |title=Cutting passes and elite ball recovery – Youri Tielemans has been transformed by Unai Emery |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5444805/2024/09/12/tielemans-transformed-emery-aston-villa/ |access-date=2025-04-12 |work=The New York Times |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref> During the [[2024–25 Premier League|2024–25 season]], Tielemans was highlighted as one of Aston Villa's best players<ref name=":3">{{Cite web |date=7 May 2025 |title=Powering Aston Villa through the season, Youri Tielemans is this year's best player |url=https://claretvillans.com/powering-aston-villa-through-the-season-youri-tielemans-is-this-year-s-best-player-01jtp0g1ar24 |access-date=2025-05-12 |website=Claret Villans |language=en-us}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Fisher |first=Ben |date=20 January 2025 |title=Youri Tielemans now the pacemaker at heart of Aston Villa's resurgence |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2025/jan/20/youri-tielemans-now-the-pacemaker-at-heart-of-aston-villas-resurgence |access-date=2025-05-12 |work=The Guardian |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref> and was praised for his footballing intelligence,<ref>{{Cite news |last=Tanswell |first=Jacob |date=4 May 2025 |title=Youri Tielemans is now Aston Villa's most important player |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/6330816/2025/05/04/youri-tielemans-aston-villa-important/ |access-date=2025-05-12 |work=The New York Times |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref> accurate shooting,<ref name=":3" /> ball recoveries and passing,<ref name=":4">{{Cite web |date=7 May 2025 |title=Youri Tielemans: Villa's do-everything midfielder |url=https://www.fotmob.com/en/topnews/21051-youri-tielemans-villas-do-everything-midfielder |access-date=2025-05-12 |website=FotMob |language=en}}</ref> with his midfield performances being compared to that of his Belgian compatriot [[Kevin De Bruyne]].<ref name=":4" /> He set a Premier League record in November 2024, completing 126 successful passes in Villa's 3–2 victory against [[Everton F.C.|Everton]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Brila |date=25 November 2024 |title=Youri Tielemans Breaks Premier League Record |url=https://www.brila.net/youri-tielemans-breaks-premier-league-record/ |access-date=2025-04-12 |website=Latest Sports News in Nigeria |language=en-US}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Tielemans was born in [[Sint-Pieters-Leeuw]], Flemish Brabant.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.worldfootball.net/person/pe323380/youri-tielemans/ |title=Youri Tielemans: Profile |website=worldfootball.net |publisher=HEIM:SPIEL |access-date=10 July 2020}}</ref> His father is of [[Flemish people|Flemish]] descent and his mother is of [[Democratic Republic of the Congo|Congolese]] descent.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Bate|first1=Adam|last2=Terreur|first2=Kristof|title=Targets: Belgium|url=http://www.skysports.com/football/news/11096/9094094/targets-belgium|access-date=30 January 2016|website=Sky Sports|date=6 January 2014}}</ref> He continued education until the age of 18, combining studies with his professional career.<ref name=sky/> As of 2020, he lived in the [[Leicestershire]] village of [[Quorn, Leicestershire|Quorn]] with his wife, Mendy, and their three daughters.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Davies |first=Matt |date=11 October 2019 |title=Leicester City star announces arrival of new baby |url=https://www.leicestermercury.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/youri-tielemans-leicester-city-baby-3419633 |access-date=2025-04-12 |website=Leicestershire Live |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Percy |first=John |date=3 October 2020 |title=Youri Tielemans exclusive interview: 'Lucky Leicester? We were just better than Manchester City' |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2020/10/03/youri-tielemans-exclusive-interview-lucky-leicester-just-better/ |access-date=2025-04-12 |work=The Telegraph |language=en-GB |issn=0307-1235}}</ref>

